Citation.sAbstract: Isothermal vapor-liquid equilibrium (VLE) data are measured for ethanol + dimethyl carbonate (DMC), DMC  + 1-propanol, and DMC + 1-butanol at T ) 333.15 K by a using headspace gas chromatography (HSGC) method.  The binary systems containing ethanol and 1-propanol have minimum boiling azeotropes. The experimental binary  VLE data were correlated with common gE model equations. Excess molar volumes (VE) of ethanol + DMC,  1-propanol + DMC, and 1-butanol + DMC are obtained from the measured densities at T ) 298.15 K by using  a digital vibrating tube densimeter. All measured VE are shown positive deviation from ideal mixing and are  correlated with the five-parameter Redlich-Kister polynomial.
Citation.sTitle: Measurement and Correlation of Vapor-Liquid Equilibria at T ) 333.15 K and Excess Molar Volumes at T ) 298.15 K for Ethanol + Dimethyl Carbonate (DMC), DMC + 1-Propanol, and DMC + 1-Butanol
